OL,3,CCharity's pay offer 'just intolerable'
OL,4,Cclaim workers as strike action begins
OL,6,FDan, a recovery navigator in the
OL,7,Fmental health service, says workers
OL,8,Fhave been offered a 2.5% pay offer.
OL,10,F"It's intolerable," he added. "Our
OL,11,Frent went up by 5.8% this year.
OL,12,FEverything is going up and our pay is
OL,13,Fbelow inflation so we're getting
OL,14,Fpoorer and something's got to give.
OL,15,FAcross the whole social care sector
OL,16,Fthis is an issue.
OL,18,F"We are fully committed to our jobs
OL,19,Fday in, day out. We need to feel
OL,20,Fsecure so that we can work as well as
OL,21,Fwe can.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
